<p>Let=E2=80=99s explain the topic <strong>Single Stage Amplifier</strong> =
and all its parts clearly =F0=9F=91=87</p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"id-5_BasicElectronics-=F0=9F=A7=A91.SingleStageAmplifier=E2=80=93=
Overview">=F0=9F=A7=A9 <strong>1. Single Stage Amplifier =E2=80=93 Overview=
</strong></h2>
<p>A <strong>single-stage amplifier</strong> uses <strong>one transistor</s=
trong> (BJT or FET) and related resistors and capacitors to amplify a weak =
input signal.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>The <strong>AC signal</strong> is applied to the input.</p></li>
<li>
<p>The <strong>amplified output</strong> is taken from the output circuit.<=
/p></li>
<li>
<p>Capacitors are used for <strong>coupling</strong> and <strong>bypassing<=
/strong> to separate AC and DC.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"id-5_BasicElectronics-=E2=9A=99=EF=B8=8F2.TypesofSingleStageAmpli=
fiers(byTransistorConfiguration)">=E2=9A=99=EF=B8=8F <strong>2. Types of Si=
ngle Stage Amplifiers (by Transistor Configuration)</strong></h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
