<h2 id=3D"id-5_BasicElectronics-=F0=9F=94=8D5.h-ParameterModel(HybridModel)=
">=F0=9F=94=8D <strong>5. h-Parameter Model (Hybrid Model)</strong></h2>
<p>The <strong>h-parameter (hybrid parameter)</strong> model represents the=
 small-signal behavior of a transistor using four parameters.<br>
It is very useful for analyzing <strong>voltage gain</strong>, <strong>curr=
ent gain</strong>, and <strong>impedance</strong> in different configuratio=
ns.</p>
<h3 id=3D"id-5_BasicElectronics-Basich-parameterequations:">Basic h-paramet=
er equations:</h3>
<p>[<br>
V_1 =3D h_{11} I_1 + h_{12} V_2<br>
]<br>
[<br>
I_2 =3D h_{21} I_1 + h_{22} V_2<br>
]</p>
<p>Where:</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"d12d5f45-4ecb-4516-90d9-784=
71c2fbc69" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Parameter</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Meaning</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Typical Unit</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>h=E2=82=81=E2=82=81</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Input impedance (hie)</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Ohm (=CE=A9)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>h=E2=82=81=E2=82=82</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Reverse voltage gain (hre)</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Dimensionless</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>h=E2=82=82=E2=82=81</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Forward current gain (hfe or =CE=B2)</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Dimensionless</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><strong>h=E2=82=82=E2=82=82</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Output admittance (hoe)</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Siemens (S)</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p>Each transistor configuration has its own h-parameter set:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Common Emitter:</strong> hie, hre, hfe, hoe</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Common Base:</strong> hib, hrb, hfb, hob</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Common Collector:</strong> hic, hrc, hfc, hoc</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
